In this room at Microsoft's headquarters in Redmond, Washington, all sound from the outside world is locked out and any sound produced inside is stopped cold.
This is the world's quietest place.
"This is a novel experience," he wrote.
Microsoft's chamber is currently registered in the Guinness World Record as the world's quietest place, a title it claimed in 2015 at the expense of a similar chamber at Orfield Labs in Minneapolis.
What are they used for? Anechoic chambers are generally used to test noises and sounds coming from a variety of products with a high degree of scientific reliability.
